      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical R2023 is a commercially validated solver with documented QA procedures including regression test suites. FDA and DePuy Synthes sites both maintain ISO 9001-compliant software validation records. Achieved level equals required level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver benchmark problems for linear and nonlinear structural analysis must demonstrate agreement within 1% of analytical solutions.",
      "rationale": "Benchmark problems including Hertzian contact, beam bending, and bolt preload were reproduced with errors below 0.8%. Code verification is documented in the solver qualification report."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study must demonstrate less than 2% change in peak von Mises stress and construct stiffness between successive refinements.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was performed on the pedicle screw shank and rod interface regions. Peak stress and construct stiffness converged to within 1.4% between the medium and fine meshes. Final mesh selected at medium refinement level for computational efficiency."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residual force and displacement norms must converge below solver default tolerances; energy balance error below 0.1%.",
      "rationale": "All nonlinear quasi-static simulations converged with force residuals below 1e-4 and displacement residuals below 1e-5. Energy balance was verified post-solution with errors below 0.05%. No divergence events were recorded across the ensemble."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented simulation execution procedures, independent review of model setup, and cross-site reproducibility checks must be in place.",
      "rationale": "Simulation execution was governed by a written protocol reviewed by all three participating sites. Independent analysts at each site reproduced key results; deviations were within inter-analyst variability bounds. Cross-site stiffness predictions agreed within 3.2%."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The constitutive model and contact formulation must be appropriate for the deformation regime and validated against representative benchmark data.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic titanium alloy material properties (Ti-6Al-4V, E=114 GPa) were used consistent with the sub-yield loading regime of the F1717 protocol. Augmented Lagrange contact formulation with friction coefficient 0.2 was selected based on prior literature. Model form is judged appropriate for the QOI range."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric dimensions must be traceable to measured or certified values with documented uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Screw and rod geometry was digitized from manufacturer drawings and verified by CMM measurements at two sites. Material coupons from the same lot were tensile-tested; measured modulus 113.8 ± 1.1 GPa. Input uncertainty propagation showed less than 2% effect on predicted stiffness."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental sample size must support statistical comparison; samples must be traceable to the same manufacturing lot as the modeled geometry.",
      "rationale": "N=11 construct specimens were drawn from a single manufacturing lot. Sample size provides 80% power to detect a 10% difference in stiffness at alpha=0.05. Specimen dimensions were measured prior to testing and fell within ±0.05 mm of nominal."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions must replicate the relevant loading environment; multiple loading conditions or rates should be evaluated where clinically relevant.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted exclusively under the standard ASTM F1717 compression-bending configuration at a single displacement rate (5 mm/min). No additional loading angles or rates were evaluated. This limitation is acknowledged; achieved level (2) falls below required level (3) for model risk level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation boundary conditions and material inputs must demonstrably correspond to experimental test conditions within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Boundary conditions in the FEA replicate the UHMWPE block fixation geometry per F1717 fixture drawings. Applied displacement ramp matches experimental protocol. Correspondence between simulation and test inputs was verified by overlay of load-displacement curves in the elastic regime."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., NRMSE, E_rel) must be defined a priori and evaluated against an acceptance threshold.",
      "rationale": "Normalized root-mean-square error (NRMSE) on construct stiffness was 4.1% across N=11 specimens, below the pre-specified 10% threshold. Predicted yield load fell within the experimental mean ± 1 SD band for 10 of 11 specimens. Comparison is judged satisfactory."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QOIs selected for comparison must be mechanistically linked to the clinical or regulatory decision metric.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield load are the primary regulatory endpoints for spinal implant mechanical performance under FDA guidance. These QOIs are directly linked to the implant's ability to maintain spinal alignment under physiological loading. Relevance is high."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The validation scenario must share geometry, material class, loading mode, and scale with the intended use scenario.",
      "rationale": "The validation activity uses the same non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw geometry, titanium alloy material class, and compression-bending loading mode as the intended simulation use. Scale and boundary conditions are identical. Validation relevance to the COU is judged high."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-noncannulated-dr-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-review-panel",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for model risk level 3. The single deficiency in Test conditions (achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is noted and accepted on the basis that the ASTM F1717 standard prescribes a single compression-bending configuration as the normative test, and no alternative loading condition is defined in the applicable regulatory submission scope. The overall credibility evidence is judged sufficient to support the intended use of this FEA model for regulatory submission purposes. The panel notes that the absence of a formally structured context-of-use record in this minimal-profile package does not alter the technical judgment; the use scope is understood from the accompanying laboratory documentation.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
